WEBVTT

00:02.803 --> 00:06.071
Honey, listen.

00:06.073 --> 00:09.074
No one can touch your mutabal.

00:09.076 --> 00:11.810
Not my mother, not your mother.

00:11.812 --> 00:13.746
I love it.

00:13.748 --> 00:17.616
I wouldn't let anybody else's
food near my mouth.
[ car door opens ]

00:17.618 --> 00:21.053
[ mouth full ] i gotta go.
There's a fare.

00:21.055 --> 00:24.089
Where to?

00:24.091 --> 00:27.960
<i>[ "the first noel" playing</i>
<i>on radio ]</i>

00:27.962 --> 00:29.228
<i>¿habla español?</i>

00:29.230 --> 00:31.964
<i>Sprechen sie deutsch?</i>

00:31.966 --> 00:34.566
<i>Peut-être français?</i>
[ zings ]

00:35.636 --> 00:37.102
Come on, man.
Where do you want --

00:37.104 --> 00:39.538
[ gasps ]
[ squish ]

00:43.177 --> 00:44.443
[ scraping ]

00:44.445 --> 00:46.045
Jo: [ voice echoing ]
...Intensely private,

00:46.047 --> 00:48.113
Borderline medical savant,

00:48.115 --> 00:52.084
And you dress pretty well
for a state worker.

00:56.791 --> 00:59.191
[ normal voice ] someday you'll
let me in when you're ready.

00:59.193 --> 01:02.861
Night, detective.

01:02.863 --> 01:05.798
[ closes car door ]
lower east side,
stanton and suffolk.

01:05.800 --> 01:07.966
Adam: Hello, henry.

01:07.968 --> 01:09.635
Buckle up.

01:09.637 --> 01:12.004
I wouldn't want you
to get hurt.

01:12.006 --> 01:13.472
[ engine revs ]

01:13.474 --> 01:15.607
<i>[ "dies irae" playing loudly ]</i>
[ tires screech ]

01:18.279 --> 01:21.013
[ horn honks ]
stop the car!

01:21.015 --> 01:23.282
Stop it!

01:23.284 --> 01:25.851
I was there the night
this premiered.

01:25.853 --> 01:28.887
Vienna was alive with mozart.

01:28.889 --> 01:30.122
[ horn honks ]

01:30.124 --> 01:32.291
I have so much to tell you,
henry,

01:32.293 --> 01:33.859
But you ignore me.

01:33.861 --> 01:36.061
[ tires screech, horn blares ]

01:36.063 --> 01:38.464
Fine, fine! We can talk!

01:38.466 --> 01:40.599
Just slow down!
Someone's gonna get killed.

01:40.601 --> 01:42.000
That's the idea.

01:42.002 --> 01:44.369
[ tires screeching,
horn blares ]

01:44.371 --> 01:46.138
See, i figured it out.

01:46.140 --> 01:48.974
You don't think i'm immortal.

01:48.976 --> 01:50.742
Guess i'll have to prove it.
No!

01:50.744 --> 01:52.010
<i>¶¶¶</i>

01:52.012 --> 01:54.046
No, don't do that!
I believe you!
[ cocks pistol ]

01:54.048 --> 01:55.814
[ gunshot ]
no!

01:55.816 --> 02:01.019
<i>¶¶¶</i>

02:01.021 --> 02:04.623
[ tires screeching,
engine revving ]

02:04.625 --> 02:07.159
No!

02:07.161 --> 02:08.594
Uhh!
[ music stops ]

02:10.331 --> 02:13.632
[ water bubbling ]

02:20.407 --> 02:22.841
Come on!

02:24.545 --> 02:27.579
[ panting ]

02:29.817 --> 02:33.552
[ grunting ]

02:36.790 --> 02:39.892
[ screaming ]

02:50.671 --> 02:53.539
[ gasps ]

02:53.541 --> 02:56.108
<i>Henry:</i>
<i>It may come as a surprise,</i>

02:56.110 --> 02:58.644
<i>But i still fear death.</i>

02:58.646 --> 03:01.980
<i>Tonight, my anonymous caller</i>
<i>faced it without hesitation.</i>

03:01.982 --> 03:05.117
<i>I realized two things</i>
<i>in that moment --</i>

03:05.119 --> 03:07.553
<i>He</i> is<i> immortal,</i>

03:07.555 --> 03:10.122
<i>And he's completely insane.</i>

03:10.124 --> 03:13.425
[ siren wailing ]

03:15.329 --> 03:17.996
Is that guy naked?

03:17.998 --> 03:21.800
Yep. Call it in.

03:21.802 --> 03:23.101
[ radio static ]

03:23.103 --> 03:25.470
[ siren wails ]

03:29.743 --> 03:32.277
So, doctor, do you often

03:32.279 --> 03:35.747
Swim naked in the east river
at night?

03:35.749 --> 03:39.117
Right. Well...

03:39.119 --> 03:40.619
It's complicated.

03:40.621 --> 03:45.324
You know, i have rarely found
the truth to be complicated.

03:47.328 --> 03:49.027
I'm a somnambulist.

03:49.029 --> 03:52.264
A sleepwalker?

03:52.266 --> 03:53.599
That's right.

03:53.601 --> 03:56.902
I pulled your file.
This is not the first time.

03:56.904 --> 03:59.104
Well,
it's a very serious condition.

03:59.106 --> 04:02.541
Sometimes i walk for blocks
and still wind up in the water.

04:02.543 --> 04:03.976
It's terribly inconvenient.

04:03.978 --> 04:05.444
And what were you doing
naked?

04:05.446 --> 04:08.313
'cause i sleep naked.

04:12.119 --> 04:13.518
You know, doctor,

04:13.520 --> 04:17.589
I've been willing to tolerate
your...Eccentricities

04:17.591 --> 04:19.424
Because
you do produce results,

04:19.426 --> 04:23.128
But i cannot have
your credibility challenged.

04:23.130 --> 04:26.198
No more night swims.

04:26.200 --> 04:28.467
Am i clear?

04:30.571 --> 04:34.473
And, doctor, please.
Invest in some pajamas.

04:34.475 --> 04:37.075
Hey, lieu, if you're done
with the skinny dipper,

04:37.077 --> 04:38.443
We got a body.

04:38.445 --> 04:39.878
[ indistinct conversations,
telephone rings ]

04:39.880 --> 04:41.480
[ laughter and applause ]

04:41.482 --> 04:43.015
Nice booking photo.

04:43.017 --> 04:45.884
Kinda chilly tonight.
[ singsongy ] here's my number.

04:45.886 --> 04:48.720
Ah, swimming cha cha
in the east river.

04:48.722 --> 04:50.722
You starting a polar bear club
without me?

04:50.724 --> 04:51.923
What?

04:51.925 --> 04:53.625
Oh, doc, i almost forgot.

04:53.627 --> 04:57.029
Um, i asked everybody
to pitch in and, uh...

04:57.031 --> 04:59.064
[ stifles laugh ]
we picked these up for ya.

04:59.066 --> 05:00.732
[ laughter ]
ow!

05:00.734 --> 05:02.901
Um, trunks optional.
[ camera shutter clicks ]

05:02.903 --> 05:06.371
Okay, some of us cops
have work to do.

05:06.373 --> 05:08.707
[ applause ]

05:08.709 --> 05:11.643
Body just arrived downstairs.
Stabbing victim.

05:11.645 --> 05:14.179
Unis found him
in a midtown dumpster.

05:14.181 --> 05:16.381
I'll start on my autopsy
immediately.

05:16.383 --> 05:18.250
Are we gonna talk about it --

05:18.252 --> 05:20.385
You swimming naked
in the east river?

05:20.387 --> 05:22.788
I'd rather not.
[ elevator bell dings ]

05:22.790 --> 05:24.723
Okay.

05:24.725 --> 05:26.258
Henry...

05:26.260 --> 05:27.859
Are you all right?

05:27.861 --> 05:30.996
[ sighs ] long night.
I'm fine.

05:30.998 --> 05:32.698
[ pushes button ]

05:37.671 --> 05:40.972
<i>[ man speaking indistinctly</i>
<i>over p.A. ]</i>

05:42.276 --> 05:44.276
First off, don't feel bad,
all right?

05:44.278 --> 05:46.411
I do plenty of stuff
in my personal life

05:46.413 --> 05:48.280
That johnny law
would frown upon.

05:48.282 --> 05:50.816
Let your freak flag fly.

05:50.818 --> 05:52.818
That's what my mom
used to say.

05:52.820 --> 05:54.820
Where's the stabbing victim,
lucas?

05:54.822 --> 05:58.290
This way. [ clears throat ]
raj patel, 31 years old.

05:58.292 --> 06:04.896
Lived in jersey. Still checking
on family and where he worked.

06:05.899 --> 06:07.566
<i>[ horn honks ]</i>

06:11.505 --> 06:13.171
He drove a cab.

06:13.173 --> 06:16.942
Duh. Obviously...Right?

06:16.944 --> 06:18.643
How would you know that?

06:21.181 --> 06:22.647
Well, telltale signs.

06:22.649 --> 06:25.250
The, uh, sun damage
on his left elbow

06:25.252 --> 06:28.854
And his gastrocnemius
on his right leg is enlarged.

06:28.856 --> 06:34.059
Make a note to jo that
there might be a missing cab.

06:34.061 --> 06:35.894
Okay.

06:35.896 --> 06:37.729
It's weird, huh?

06:37.731 --> 06:39.731
I mean, there's no mark
on his entire body

06:39.733 --> 06:42.134
Except for the puncture wound,
and it goes straight through.

06:42.136 --> 06:46.138
This man was killed
with one precise thrust

06:46.140 --> 06:48.140
Through the spine,
heart, and sternum.

06:48.142 --> 06:50.642
It would have taken
incredible skill, strength,

06:50.644 --> 06:52.744
And a special blade.

06:52.746 --> 06:55.480
No. A sword.

06:55.482 --> 06:57.416
A sword. Gotcha.

06:57.418 --> 07:01.286
Okay. I'll put an a.P.B.
Out for the highlander.
[ gloves snap ]

07:01.288 --> 07:02.587
Who?

07:02.589 --> 07:04.456
The highlander?

07:04.458 --> 07:06.958
Christopher lambert,
sean connery.

07:06.960 --> 07:08.927
"there can be only one."

07:08.929 --> 07:11.096
Nothin'?

07:11.098 --> 07:13.532
You know what? Forget it.

07:13.534 --> 07:15.934
¶¶¶

07:22.075 --> 07:23.208
Henry, please tell me

07:23.210 --> 07:24.810
You're not challenging
the caller to a duel.

07:24.812 --> 07:26.445
This is research. I have
to get back to the lab.

07:26.447 --> 07:29.247
Wait. What are you doing?

07:29.249 --> 07:30.782
My job.
Are you crazy?

07:30.784 --> 07:32.317
You're being stalked
by a psychopath

07:32.319 --> 07:33.752
Who can't be killed.

07:33.754 --> 07:36.254
You don't understand.
He's killed someone else --

07:36.256 --> 07:37.923
A cab driver, raj patel.

07:37.925 --> 07:40.325
I find raj's killer,
i find the caller.

07:40.327 --> 07:42.060
You -- you can't do this
by yourself.

07:42.062 --> 07:43.195
What are you saying?

07:43.197 --> 07:44.663
With the caller out there,
you need help --

07:44.665 --> 07:45.864
Someone you can trust.

07:45.866 --> 07:47.299
I've already got someone
i can trust.

07:47.301 --> 07:51.770
No, no. Someone --
someone -- someone with a badge.

07:51.772 --> 07:52.871
Jo?

07:52.873 --> 07:54.940
This guy's got 2,000 years
experience.

07:54.942 --> 07:57.275
What are you gonna do
when you find him?

07:57.277 --> 07:58.543
What are you gonna do then,
huh?

07:58.545 --> 08:00.745
Just ask him to stop?
Politely?

08:00.747 --> 08:03.148
Tell jo about me
and the anonymous caller?

08:03.150 --> 08:04.382
She'll think i'm insane.

08:04.384 --> 08:06.084
Henry, henry, you need her.

08:06.086 --> 08:09.221
Hell, you might need
the entire n.Y.P.D.

08:09.223 --> 08:10.689
But you can trust her.

08:10.691 --> 08:13.158
I've done that before.

08:13.160 --> 08:15.026
It ended poorly.

08:15.028 --> 08:16.528
<i>Stop it!</i>

08:16.530 --> 08:17.963
There's been a mistake!

08:17.965 --> 08:19.931
Nora, please tell them
there's been a mistake!

08:19.933 --> 08:23.168
I just want you to get better!
Nora!

08:23.170 --> 08:24.503
[ door closes ]

08:24.505 --> 08:26.671
[ moaning and screaming
in distance ]

08:26.673 --> 08:30.041
Look. Look at me.

08:30.043 --> 08:32.978
I'm not mad.

08:32.980 --> 08:35.213
Simply tell the doctor
this was a mistake,

08:35.215 --> 08:36.748
That you were mistaken.

08:36.750 --> 08:38.049
Was i?

08:38.051 --> 08:40.819
Was i mistaken when you put
that knife to your wrist?

08:40.821 --> 08:45.590
Well, i had to show someone.
And you're my wife.

08:48.195 --> 08:51.129
I trust you.

08:56.336 --> 08:58.370
[ sighs ] forgive me.

08:58.372 --> 09:00.639
Nora, don't do this!

09:01.875 --> 09:05.477
You're sick, henry.
They can help you here.

09:05.479 --> 09:07.078
Nora?

09:07.080 --> 09:10.615
Nora? Nora!

09:11.485 --> 09:12.617
Steady, lucas.

09:12.619 --> 09:14.085
It's deceptively heavy.

09:14.087 --> 09:15.453
Well, that's wrong.

09:15.455 --> 09:18.490
Well, after 10 minutes
like this, i think you'd agree.

09:18.492 --> 09:20.859
No. I mean, it's not
the right sword.

09:20.861 --> 09:23.395
The blade that killed raj
is 9 millimeters wider

09:23.397 --> 09:24.629
Than the rapier.

09:24.631 --> 09:25.630
Hanson: Ahem.

09:25.632 --> 09:27.699
Ah, detectives.

09:27.701 --> 09:29.167
We're ready for you.

09:29.169 --> 09:32.437
Raj patel was killed
with a single-edged sword.

09:32.439 --> 09:35.707
The thrust went through his back
and exited his torso --

09:35.709 --> 09:37.342
A swift, clinical murder.

09:37.344 --> 09:38.743
Jeez. Look at that.

09:38.745 --> 09:40.612
All that to steal a cab?

09:40.614 --> 09:42.881
What can you tell us
about raj?

09:42.883 --> 09:44.983
Well, driving is sedentary work,

09:44.985 --> 09:46.718
But judging
from his recent striae

09:46.720 --> 09:50.021
On his bilateral overhangs --
stretch marks
on his love handles.

09:50.023 --> 09:52.524
And his erythematous
subcondyle...
Lucas: Sunburn on his elbow.

09:52.526 --> 09:55.327
And his lack of hemorrhoids...
No translation necessary.

09:55.329 --> 09:58.063
All suggest that he hadn't
been a cabbie for very long.

09:58.065 --> 09:59.664
Oh, by the way,
detective hanson,

09:59.666 --> 10:00.832
You might consider
a standing desk

10:00.834 --> 10:02.067
For that condition.

10:02.069 --> 10:04.402
What...Condition?
[ cell phone rings ]

10:04.404 --> 10:05.637
Uh, h-hold on.
[ beep ]

10:05.639 --> 10:06.905
Hanson here.

10:06.907 --> 10:09.074
Uh, what did you get
off the tox report?

10:09.076 --> 10:11.576
Came back clean.
No drugs. No alcohol.

10:11.578 --> 10:13.044
One little blip here --

10:13.046 --> 10:15.647
He was recently given
a hepatitis b vaccination.

10:15.649 --> 10:17.916
Which is standard
for medical professionals,

10:17.918 --> 10:19.317
But unusual for a cab driver.

10:19.319 --> 10:21.586
Yeah, young cabbies often
have a second job.

10:21.588 --> 10:23.355
Maybe he was working
at a hospital, too.

10:23.357 --> 10:27.659
Have you had any luck in finding
the cab itself, detective?

10:27.661 --> 10:30.228
It may no longer be...
On manhattan.

10:30.230 --> 10:32.998
Good guess, doc. Water cops
just spotted something submerged

10:33.000 --> 10:35.233
In the hudson
right off of pier 40.

10:35.235 --> 10:38.169
It's -- it's our taxi.
They're pulling it out now.

10:38.171 --> 10:40.972
[ police radio chatter ]

10:40.974 --> 10:44.275
[ indistinct conversations ]

11:00.594 --> 11:02.727
<i>[ engine revs ]</i>

11:02.729 --> 11:05.363
Henry? You comin'?

11:05.365 --> 11:07.565
Yes, of course.

11:07.567 --> 11:11.036
[ police radio chatter
continues ]

11:20.580 --> 11:21.713
Hey, jo, do you see this?

11:21.715 --> 11:24.749
Yep. It looks like
your sword

11:24.751 --> 11:26.151
Went right
through the seat.

11:26.153 --> 11:27.819
All right,
what's the theory here?

11:27.821 --> 11:29.454
Passenger with sword
stabs raj the driver

11:29.456 --> 11:30.689
When they're stopped.

11:30.691 --> 11:33.024
Passenger dumps the body,
drives here,

11:33.026 --> 11:35.760
And then launches the cab
into the hudson?

11:35.762 --> 11:36.895
Is that it?

11:36.897 --> 11:38.096
Hey, look at this window.

11:38.098 --> 11:39.597
These fragments
make it look like

11:39.599 --> 11:41.599
It was blown up
from the inside.

11:41.601 --> 11:44.502
No.

11:44.504 --> 11:45.503
It was shot out.

11:45.505 --> 11:47.906
Somebody fired a gun?

11:47.908 --> 11:50.241
Maybe the cabbie tried
to shoot the passenger.

11:50.243 --> 11:51.776
<i>No, don't do that!</i>
<i>[ gunshot ]</i>

11:51.778 --> 11:54.312
Well, it couldn't have been raj.

11:54.314 --> 11:56.981
The sword would have killed him
almost instantly.

11:56.983 --> 11:58.216
Yeah, raj didn't own a gun,

11:58.218 --> 11:59.918
At least not one
registered to him.

11:59.920 --> 12:02.520
Ever see a casing like this?

12:02.522 --> 12:04.289
My father was a gun collector.

12:04.291 --> 12:06.624
This is a 7.63 millimeter
shell casing.

12:06.626 --> 12:10.295
It's from an old automatic.
Like, turn of the century, jo.

12:10.297 --> 12:13.064
Now what would a cabbie be doing
carrying an antique gun?

12:13.066 --> 12:14.466
Could have been
the killer's.

12:14.468 --> 12:17.135
Maybe this guy has
an antique weapon fetish.

12:17.137 --> 12:20.505
Sounds like your dream case,
doc. What are you thinkin'?

12:23.944 --> 12:26.444
<i>[ screams ]</i>

12:29.483 --> 12:33.785
Whoa. Looks like somebody
was desperate to get out.

12:35.155 --> 12:36.488
Henry?

12:36.490 --> 12:38.156
Sorry. You were saying?

12:38.158 --> 12:42.293
Those scratches --
you think we can pull d.N.A.?

12:42.295 --> 12:43.361
[ exhales deeply ]

12:43.363 --> 12:47.365
Well, with all this water,
i doubt it.

13:03.183 --> 13:04.449
Henry.

13:04.451 --> 13:06.317
This is your watch.

13:07.821 --> 13:09.487
What?

13:12.726 --> 13:15.093
Yeah,
you must've dropped it.

13:17.164 --> 13:18.463
Thank you.

13:18.465 --> 13:20.865
Try not to go contaminating
the crime scene, doc.

13:20.867 --> 13:23.735
You don't want us thinking
<i>you're</i> the killer, right?

13:23.737 --> 13:27.338
That would be shocking.

13:33.580 --> 13:34.813
[ horn honks in distance ]

13:34.815 --> 13:37.182
[ vehicle passes ]

13:37.884 --> 13:39.517
[ door rattles ]

13:40.821 --> 13:42.887
[ whistle blows ]

13:42.889 --> 13:45.557
[ door bells jingle ]

13:47.894 --> 13:51.663
[ siren wailing in distance ]

13:51.665 --> 13:54.165
We've been in the antique
business for 20 years,

13:54.167 --> 13:56.334
And never have we been
by appointment only.

13:56.336 --> 13:58.236
A temporary change made
by management

13:58.238 --> 14:00.238
Due to the present
security situation

14:00.240 --> 14:02.273
Involving
unkillable psychopaths.

14:02.275 --> 14:03.641
I need your help.

14:03.643 --> 14:04.742
Did you tell jo?

14:04.744 --> 14:06.244
[ sighs ]
she's after a killer

14:06.246 --> 14:08.179
With a penchant
for antique weapons.

14:08.181 --> 14:10.682
Anything else i tell her
will make me sound insane.

14:10.684 --> 14:14.052
Henry, this guy calls you
from time to time on the phone.

14:14.054 --> 14:17.288
She should know that.
Will you please help me?

14:17.290 --> 14:19.724
You are incredible.
Yes, of course i'll help you.

14:19.726 --> 14:21.292
What do you need?

14:24.531 --> 14:25.930
Anything over there?

14:25.932 --> 14:27.165
I've got bupkes.

14:27.167 --> 14:29.801
This is ridiculous,
you know that?

14:29.803 --> 14:31.069
Well, have faith.

14:31.071 --> 14:32.470
Based on my calculations,

14:32.472 --> 14:34.939
The cab impacted the water
over there,

14:34.941 --> 14:36.908
Meaning the gun
shouldn't be far.

14:36.910 --> 14:38.276
How do you know that?

14:38.278 --> 14:42.013
In 1904, a steamboat
sank in these waters.

14:42.015 --> 14:43.314
Interestingly enough,

14:43.316 --> 14:45.016
The offshore current pushed
most of the debris

14:45.018 --> 14:46.918
This way under the pier.

14:46.920 --> 14:49.821
Meaning?
Have faith in the plan.

14:49.823 --> 14:51.356
I have a lot of faith,
you know,

14:51.358 --> 14:53.157
In you, in me,
in the yankees.

14:53.159 --> 14:55.093
This<i> fakakta</i> plan --
not so much.

14:55.095 --> 14:57.161
It's going to work.

14:57.163 --> 14:59.430
How does jo put up
with you, hmm?

14:59.432 --> 15:02.600
You're very cocky
with the theories, you know?

15:02.602 --> 15:07.305
Oh! I think i found it.

15:07.307 --> 15:09.173
That it?

15:09.175 --> 15:11.042
Oh, well done, abraham.

15:11.044 --> 15:12.243
Hmm.
[ ship horn blowing ]

15:12.245 --> 15:14.178
Mm, it's too deep to reach.

15:14.180 --> 15:16.080
Good. Let's go home.
Are you kidding?

15:16.082 --> 15:17.649
One quick dip,
and it's ours.

15:17.651 --> 15:19.250
Oh, no, no, no,
please, don't do this.

15:19.252 --> 15:20.985
Don't do this. Come on.
It's very cold out.

15:20.987 --> 15:22.553
It's like a summer's day
in england.

15:22.555 --> 15:23.988
I can see your breath.

15:23.990 --> 15:26.057
Henry.

15:26.059 --> 15:29.060
Oh, my god.

15:29.062 --> 15:30.628
I mean, do you know how cold
that water is?

15:30.630 --> 15:32.864
And there a lot of very,
very strange things in there,

15:32.866 --> 15:34.032
Aside from guns.

15:34.034 --> 15:36.000
Well, i shall add
to the mixture.

15:36.002 --> 15:38.336
Oh, for god's sake.

15:41.608 --> 15:43.074
Where did you get those?

15:43.076 --> 15:46.544
A gift
from detective hanson.

15:46.546 --> 15:48.880
I'm not gonna ask.

15:48.882 --> 15:50.481
Will you just --
just be very care--

15:50.483 --> 15:51.883
Care-- careful.

15:51.885 --> 15:53.017
[ exhales deeply ]

15:53.019 --> 15:54.686
[ siren whoops ]

15:54.688 --> 15:55.853
Great.
Male officer:
[ amplified voice ] sir, please

15:55.855 --> 15:57.689
Step away from the ledge.

15:59.859 --> 16:03.161
Hey, fellas.
What's going on?

16:03.163 --> 16:06.130
[ sighs ] we're on
official police business.

16:06.132 --> 16:08.132
Uh, semi-official.

16:08.134 --> 16:09.634
Oh, sure you are.

16:09.636 --> 16:11.436
Why don't you come over here,
and we'll talk about it?

16:11.438 --> 16:15.006
Two arrests
for indecent exposure

16:15.008 --> 16:17.175
In less than 48 hours?

16:17.177 --> 16:19.043
What am i supposed to do
with you?

16:19.045 --> 16:20.511
I can explain.

16:20.513 --> 16:22.380
What, it's the --
the sleepwalking again?

16:22.382 --> 16:24.882
No! This has to do
with the case.

16:24.884 --> 16:26.551
We found a shell
in the car --

16:26.553 --> 16:28.853
A unique caliber
to an antique gun.

16:28.855 --> 16:30.688
It's in the water
under the pier.

16:30.690 --> 16:33.124
If we retrieve it,
it may lead us to our killer.

16:33.126 --> 16:34.792
And why didn't you
come to me?

16:34.794 --> 16:36.461
Perhaps i should have.

16:36.463 --> 16:38.262
That might have been
the right thing to do,

16:38.264 --> 16:40.465
But i was worried
that you might say "no,"

16:40.467 --> 16:42.200
And there really isn't
much time to waste.

16:42.202 --> 16:45.603
There is a killer out there,
and we need to find him now!

16:51.177 --> 16:52.477
I do beg your pardon.

16:52.479 --> 16:54.812
I have no idea
why i'm shouting.

16:54.814 --> 16:57.048
Perhaps i should
stop talking now

16:57.050 --> 16:59.217
And await your verdict.
[ sighs ]

16:59.219 --> 17:01.352
Jo:
Another naked swim? Really?

17:01.354 --> 17:03.321
I wasn't completely naked.

17:03.323 --> 17:04.889
Will you please
send someone to the pier?

17:04.891 --> 17:06.958
The gun from the cab is
in the water near the landing.

17:06.960 --> 17:08.459
What did reece say?

17:08.461 --> 17:11.295
[ sighs ] i need to see
a therapist.

17:11.297 --> 17:12.997
Well, every cop gets sent
to bellevue

17:12.999 --> 17:14.365
To sit with a shrink.

17:14.367 --> 17:16.601
It's okay.
Our job is stressful.

17:16.603 --> 17:19.103
I'm fine.
I don't need a therapist.

17:19.105 --> 17:21.506
Take it from me.
It builds up.

17:21.508 --> 17:23.174
So many years
of doing this job,

17:23.176 --> 17:25.510
You need somebody
to talk to.

17:25.512 --> 17:30.048
If you need someone,
i'm here.

17:32.986 --> 17:34.786
You know what? [ sighs ]

17:34.788 --> 17:37.388
Go talk to the therapist.

17:37.390 --> 17:39.557
What's the worst
that could happen?

17:44.731 --> 17:46.397
[ screaming in distance ]

17:46.399 --> 17:49.834
You are a sane man,
dr. Morgan,

17:49.836 --> 17:52.003
With a clear conscience,

17:52.005 --> 17:54.972
An unclouded mind.
That's obvious.

17:54.974 --> 17:57.241
Yes. Yes, i am.

17:57.243 --> 18:00.211
Which makes it all
the more difficult to understand

18:00.213 --> 18:04.248
Why you would tell your wife
that you are immortal,

18:04.250 --> 18:06.884
Why you would believe,
in that moment,

18:06.886 --> 18:10.555
Something that any sane man
would know is impossible.

18:10.557 --> 18:12.223
I'm not an immortal.

18:12.225 --> 18:15.493
[ breathing heavily ]
i wasn't in my...Right mind

18:15.495 --> 18:17.862
When i said those words
to nora.

18:17.864 --> 18:22.166
I have since...
Come back to my senses.

18:22.168 --> 18:25.169
Perhaps. But we must be
scientific

18:25.171 --> 18:28.539
To ensure that it does not
happen again.

18:28.541 --> 18:32.577
I am prescribing
a new treatment for you.

18:32.579 --> 18:35.713
Have you heard
of hydrotherapy?

18:35.715 --> 18:36.981
No.

18:36.983 --> 18:42.320
Good.
It is very scientific.

18:42.322 --> 18:47.992
[ moaning and screaming
in distance ]

18:47.994 --> 18:50.061
[ whistling ]

18:50.063 --> 18:53.164
[ whistling stops ]
[ british accent ]
you seem anxious, dr. Morgan.

18:53.166 --> 18:55.666
I'm fine, dr. Farber.
Completely fine.

18:55.668 --> 18:58.302
I see. Now...

18:58.304 --> 19:00.138
How do you take it?

19:00.140 --> 19:03.908
One lump, please.
Milk first. Thank you.

19:03.910 --> 19:05.476
[ dishes clatter ]

19:05.478 --> 19:09.480
Nice cup of darjeeling
to help the medicine go down.

19:09.482 --> 19:11.883
Have you ever been
to therapy

19:11.885 --> 19:14.619
Or worked with a psychiatrist
before?

19:14.621 --> 19:17.221
This is my first trip
to bellevue.

19:17.223 --> 19:18.489
Ah. Welcome, then.

19:18.491 --> 19:20.658
Did lieutenant reece
tell you

19:20.660 --> 19:23.127
How many sessions
are required, dr. Farber?

19:23.129 --> 19:24.595
The number's up to me,

19:24.597 --> 19:26.330
And, uh, please,
call me "lewis."

19:26.332 --> 19:28.232
May i call you "henry"?

19:28.234 --> 19:32.370
Great. So...

19:32.372 --> 19:34.071
You're a londoner?

19:34.073 --> 19:35.706
Yes, yes, originally.

19:35.708 --> 19:39.043
It's great to hear
a, uh, english accent.

19:39.045 --> 19:40.311
We brits must
stick together.

19:40.313 --> 19:41.712
You followed
your wife here?

19:41.714 --> 19:43.481
Yes --

19:43.483 --> 19:47.084
Ah, now i've heard
about your sherlockian gifts.

19:47.086 --> 19:48.586
What gave me away?

19:48.588 --> 19:49.620
In the pictures,

19:49.622 --> 19:51.522
Your wife's hair
is cut in the fashion

19:51.524 --> 19:53.391
To de-emphasize
her attractiveness

19:53.393 --> 19:55.359
And enhance authority --

19:55.361 --> 19:56.928
Common
to corporate executives.

19:56.930 --> 20:00.064
Your degree from oxford is
impressive -- congratulations --

20:00.066 --> 20:03.000
But hardly lucrative enough
to justify moving one's family.

20:03.002 --> 20:04.402
She's got a great job.

20:04.404 --> 20:07.338
Now we shouldn't be
really talking about me.

20:07.340 --> 20:10.675
But, um...Can i ask...

20:10.677 --> 20:12.877
Do you ever really feel
at home here?

20:12.879 --> 20:14.912
It's just, uh, i've been
here nearly a year,

20:14.914 --> 20:17.915
And i still sense
i'm out of place.

20:20.453 --> 20:22.019
That never goes away.

20:22.021 --> 20:24.222
Hmm.
[ teacup clatters ]

20:24.224 --> 20:26.057
And when you feel
like that,

20:26.059 --> 20:28.159
Who do you talk to?

20:28.161 --> 20:32.263
Is this it?
Is...This...Therapy?

20:32.265 --> 20:34.665
[ chuckles ]
it just started.

20:34.667 --> 20:38.436
I ask the questions,
and you answer how you like.

20:38.438 --> 20:41.105
I believe that we all
need a person that we can

20:41.107 --> 20:43.841
Share our secrets with,
someone we can trust.

20:43.843 --> 20:47.011
Now that could be me.
Uh, could be a friend.

20:47.013 --> 20:49.747
I have abe.

20:49.749 --> 20:50.848
And who is abe?

20:50.850 --> 20:53.050
We share a small
antique shop in the city.

20:53.052 --> 20:55.052
He's a friend.

20:55.054 --> 20:58.055
And how about at work --

20:58.057 --> 20:59.557
Someone closer
to your own age?

20:59.559 --> 21:03.461
What about, um,
detective martinez?

21:03.463 --> 21:05.396
Can you trust her?

21:07.667 --> 21:10.668
[ indistinct conversations,
telephone rings in distance ]

21:10.670 --> 21:12.003
Henry was right.

21:12.005 --> 21:14.038
Divers found it right where
dr. Crazy crackers

21:14.040 --> 21:15.172
Said it would be.

21:15.174 --> 21:16.674
What is it?

21:16.676 --> 21:19.477
That is a c96 mauser.
Early prototype. Super rare.

21:19.479 --> 21:21.345
But that's not the most
exciting part here, jo.

21:21.347 --> 21:23.214
That gun is registered
to a brooklyn address --

21:23.216 --> 21:25.216
One richard smight.

21:25.218 --> 21:27.485
How'd you like to go
kick down a door?

21:27.487 --> 21:28.986
You gotta ask?

21:29.956 --> 21:33.758
Look, i like what
i've found here in new york.

21:33.760 --> 21:35.960
Working with jo...

21:35.962 --> 21:38.229
[ sighs ]

21:38.231 --> 21:39.830
I'd hate to lose that.

21:39.832 --> 21:42.733
[ man shouting indistinctly,
door creaks ]

21:44.504 --> 21:48.439
[ man and woman arguing
indistinctly ]

21:48.441 --> 21:50.041
[ knocks on door ]

21:50.043 --> 21:51.509
Mr. Smight?

21:51.511 --> 21:52.910
Dr. Farber: This is only
your first session,

21:52.912 --> 21:55.446
And you certainly
don't have to answer this

21:55.448 --> 21:58.316
If you don't want to,
but...

21:58.318 --> 22:01.852
What exactly
are you afraid of?

22:04.390 --> 22:06.390
Someone getting hurt...

22:06.392 --> 22:07.692
Because of me.

22:07.694 --> 22:11.095
Jo: Richard?
It's detective martinez

22:11.097 --> 22:12.863
With the n.Y.P.D.

22:12.865 --> 22:14.865
Please open the door?

22:14.867 --> 22:16.434
[ door creaks ]

22:17.937 --> 22:21.205
Mr. Smight?
We're gonna come in.

22:21.207 --> 22:23.808
[ door creaks ]

22:42.829 --> 22:47.131
[ creaks ]

22:51.537 --> 22:54.338
What the hell is that?

22:54.340 --> 22:55.906
[ gasps ]

22:55.908 --> 22:57.108
Our new victim,

22:57.110 --> 23:01.145
Except somebody's already
performed the autopsy.

23:01.147 --> 23:04.582
[ sighs ]
call henry.

23:07.854 --> 23:09.019
[ siren wailing in distance ]

23:09.021 --> 23:11.422
[ sighs ] we have a name?

23:11.424 --> 23:12.957
Richard smight.

23:12.959 --> 23:15.659
Landlords say he's lived here
for about five years.

23:15.661 --> 23:16.927
Keeps to himself, mostly.

23:16.929 --> 23:19.163
Looks like he was autopsied,
right?

23:19.165 --> 23:21.866
But this wasn't an autopsy.

23:21.868 --> 23:24.301
An autopsy can only be
performed on the dead.

23:24.303 --> 23:26.404
This man was still alive.

23:26.406 --> 23:28.205
The autopsy was
the cause of death.

23:28.207 --> 23:30.975
Do you see any connection
between this guy and raj?

23:30.977 --> 23:35.446
Yes. Both men were killed
with incredible precision.

23:35.448 --> 23:38.716
This man was cut open
with a drop point blade,

23:38.718 --> 23:41.185
Like a hunting knife -- no.

23:41.187 --> 23:44.121
Exactly like a hunting knife.

23:50.029 --> 23:51.762
Hey. What's up, buddy?

23:56.903 --> 23:58.235
Excuse me.

23:58.237 --> 24:01.238
Henry.

24:01.240 --> 24:03.441
What's up with him?

24:05.244 --> 24:07.812
He uses a hunting knife.

24:09.649 --> 24:11.582
Lucas, where are my tools?

24:11.584 --> 24:13.317
Where they always are.

24:13.319 --> 24:16.086
What's going on?

24:18.090 --> 24:20.658
[ rustling ]

24:23.095 --> 24:26.197
[ tools clattering ]

24:29.402 --> 24:30.534
See?

24:30.536 --> 24:32.736
Right where
they always are,

24:32.738 --> 24:36.140
In perfect condition,
sharpened and cleaned.

24:52.959 --> 24:55.593
Everything okay?

24:56.929 --> 24:57.928
Yes.

24:57.930 --> 24:59.697
I have to pop out
for a moment.

24:59.699 --> 25:01.899
Prep mr. Smight
when he comes in.

25:01.901 --> 25:03.167
I won't be long.

25:03.169 --> 25:04.568
[ tools clatter ]

25:04.570 --> 25:05.703
[ glass clinks ]

25:05.705 --> 25:07.037
[ door bells jingle ]

25:07.039 --> 25:09.373
Ah, sorry.
By appointment only.

25:09.375 --> 25:10.641
I think you may be right.

25:10.643 --> 25:12.109
[ thud ]
what happened?

25:12.111 --> 25:14.545
He's upped the ante.
The caller's killing people

25:14.547 --> 25:16.247
In order to frame me
for murder.

25:16.249 --> 25:17.815
Listen, henry,
i heard enough.

25:17.817 --> 25:20.217
You gotta pack your things.
I'll get my gear. We gotta go.

25:20.219 --> 25:23.187
But that's what he wants.
He's forcing us to leave.

25:23.189 --> 25:25.956
Stripping away my life,
piece by piece. Why?

25:25.958 --> 25:27.258
We're not gonna stay here
to find out.

25:27.260 --> 25:29.927
You cannot stay and fight,
not by yourself.

25:29.929 --> 25:31.562
We gotta do whatever
we've always done.

25:31.564 --> 25:33.531
We gotta get outta town or --
or?

25:33.533 --> 25:36.000
Or you call jo.
Tell the police.

25:36.002 --> 25:39.470
Well, they'd never believe me.
We're running.

25:39.472 --> 25:41.906
[ footsteps depart ]

25:43.609 --> 25:46.243
Lucas?
Hey, where's henry?

25:46.245 --> 25:47.912
I need to look
at richard smight's report.

25:47.914 --> 25:51.448
Oh. I guess he stepped out.
Yeah. He should be back...

25:51.450 --> 25:52.983
S-soonish.

25:52.985 --> 25:54.552
What's wrong?

25:54.554 --> 25:56.554
Nothing. I --
lucas.

25:56.556 --> 25:58.088
Look, i don't know.

25:58.090 --> 26:00.958
Okay? I mean, we usually
go over the bodies together

26:00.960 --> 26:04.728
Right when they come in,
and this time, he just...Split.

26:04.730 --> 26:08.198
And this body
is super creeping me out.

26:08.200 --> 26:09.366
Why?

26:09.368 --> 26:10.734
What's creeping me out
is the way

26:10.736 --> 26:12.636
That the autopsy
was performed.

26:12.638 --> 26:15.139
I mean, the flourishes
and the scalpel marks.

26:15.141 --> 26:18.776
Look...Every m.E.
Is a painter,

26:18.778 --> 26:21.612
Right? And they have
brushstrokes, and...

26:21.614 --> 26:23.948
[ inhales sharply ] well...

26:25.251 --> 26:27.851
These are henry's.

26:31.223 --> 26:32.957
[ thud ]

26:35.027 --> 26:36.126
Five minutes!

26:36.128 --> 26:37.528
Henry: Almost ready.

26:37.530 --> 26:40.764
I just need to grab
a few more things.

26:43.235 --> 26:44.935
[ door bells jingle ]

26:48.674 --> 26:52.676
[ footsteps approach ]

27:00.353 --> 27:02.920
[ stairs creak ]

27:09.895 --> 27:13.197
[ stairs continue creaking ]

27:16.802 --> 27:20.671
[ footsteps approach ]

27:20.673 --> 27:22.272
Jo: Henry?

27:25.578 --> 27:29.046
[ sighs ] it's not what
you think it is.

27:35.721 --> 27:37.721
Actually, it's exactly
what you think it is.

27:37.723 --> 27:39.790
It's the murder weapon,

27:39.792 --> 27:41.725
The one used to kill
richard smight,

27:41.727 --> 27:43.661
The second victim.

27:43.663 --> 27:45.896
Why do you have it?

27:52.438 --> 27:55.439
Well...

27:55.441 --> 27:58.175
It's mine.

28:02.081 --> 28:03.847
Henry, what the hell
is going on?

28:03.849 --> 28:06.617
It's --
don't you dare say
it's complicated.

28:06.619 --> 28:09.687
I need the truth
right now.

28:11.724 --> 28:14.191
Why do you have that?

28:16.896 --> 28:18.729
You won't believe me.

28:18.731 --> 28:22.232
Try me. As your friend,
i am giving you

28:22.234 --> 28:25.769
The chance
to explain yourself.

28:25.771 --> 28:29.173
Just tell me the truth.

28:31.377 --> 28:35.245
Henry, tell her.

28:39.452 --> 28:43.087
<i>Tell me again the truth.</i>

28:43.089 --> 28:45.589
Are you immortal?
[ breathing heavily ]

28:45.591 --> 28:48.625
I was confused before.

28:48.627 --> 28:52.663
I'm a man.
I know that now.

28:52.665 --> 28:55.332
You're lying...Again.

28:55.334 --> 28:57.067
No. No, please.

28:57.069 --> 28:59.770
[ crying ] please.
For god's sake.

28:59.772 --> 29:06.076
I'm not immortal!
No! [ sobbing ] no! No!

29:06.078 --> 29:10.848
No! No! No! [ coughs ]

29:12.485 --> 29:17.755
Henry, tell us everything.
No more secrets.

29:24.630 --> 29:27.831
[ sighs ]

29:27.833 --> 29:31.101
I have a stalker.

29:32.938 --> 29:35.572
Began a few months ago
with an anonymous call.

29:35.574 --> 29:39.343
I thought it was nothing
to worry anyone about.

29:39.345 --> 29:44.515
Just a lonely person
with an obsession with death.

29:44.517 --> 29:48.485
But i soon realized
that he was disturbed --

29:48.487 --> 29:51.021
Insane, really.

29:51.023 --> 29:52.790
He believes
that he's immortal.

29:52.792 --> 29:53.924
Immortal?

29:53.926 --> 29:55.459
Yeah. [ chuckles ]

29:55.461 --> 29:58.162
I stopped talking to him,
and i thought it was over,

29:58.164 --> 30:00.330
But when i saw
the second body,

30:00.332 --> 30:01.465
The autopsied man,

30:01.467 --> 30:04.535
I realized that
my stalker was the killer

30:04.537 --> 30:08.472
And that he'd done it
using my tools.

30:08.474 --> 30:11.074
Why were you leaving town?

30:14.747 --> 30:17.781
Because i thought
it might stop him.

30:17.783 --> 30:19.016
He's obsessed.

30:19.018 --> 30:22.753
If i'm here,
he<i> will</i> kill again.

30:22.755 --> 30:27.391
Lieu, henry was with a therapist
when we found the body.

30:27.393 --> 30:29.493
You can't think
that he would p--

30:33.032 --> 30:37.167
I should have told you.
You have --

30:37.169 --> 30:42.506
You all have every reason
to suspect that it was me.

30:44.743 --> 30:46.376
Henry?

30:51.250 --> 30:55.185
We're gonna catch
this son of a bitch.

30:55.187 --> 30:58.255
This guy got into our building.

30:58.257 --> 31:00.524
Get me surveillance
on the o.C.M.E.

31:00.526 --> 31:01.925
And then lock it down.

31:01.927 --> 31:04.695
I want a task force
up and running a.S.A.P.

31:04.697 --> 31:07.297
This is our priority.

31:10.202 --> 31:14.137
Dr. Morgan, i know
you've been through a lot.

31:14.139 --> 31:17.474
But i'm gonna need the autopsy
on that last victim.

31:17.476 --> 31:20.944
Give me something
to catch this killer.

31:29.088 --> 31:33.156
Oh. Found something.
A bite mark.

31:38.697 --> 31:40.197
Those are human teeth.

31:40.199 --> 31:41.531
Oh.

31:41.533 --> 31:44.768
The cabbie was recently
vaccinated for hepatitis b.

31:44.770 --> 31:45.836
Yeah.

31:45.838 --> 31:46.970
What about this man?

31:46.972 --> 31:50.774
Uh, mr. Smight...

31:50.776 --> 31:52.509
Received a vaccine
six months ago.

31:52.511 --> 31:55.345
Well, that's more
than a coincidence.

31:55.347 --> 31:56.513
What do we have?

31:56.515 --> 31:59.850
They were both vaccinated
for hepatitis b.

31:59.852 --> 32:01.518
Could they have been
working together?

32:01.520 --> 32:06.523
Um...Smight was...
An orderly at bellevue.

32:06.525 --> 32:08.992
The oldest psychiatric hospital
in new york city.

32:08.994 --> 32:10.394
Yeah, he'd have to be
vaccinated.

32:10.396 --> 32:12.462
Raj's last job was
with a security firm --

32:12.464 --> 32:15.132
Titan security.

32:15.134 --> 32:18.335
They handle most of the security
for the city's hospitals.

32:18.337 --> 32:22.339
You're right. Bellevue might
just be our connection.

32:23.742 --> 32:25.242
[ horns honking in distance ]

32:25.244 --> 32:28.545
Hey, i spoke with h.R.

32:28.547 --> 32:30.380
Both victims worked here,
and both left

32:30.382 --> 32:33.116
Due to a physical altercation
with the same patient.

32:33.118 --> 32:34.818
Which patient?
They won't tell us.

32:34.820 --> 32:37.754
We need a court order
to open the patient files.

32:37.756 --> 32:39.056
[ sighs ]
there's no time for this.

32:39.058 --> 32:40.123
Yeah, well,
unless you're a psychiatrist,

32:40.125 --> 32:41.658
We wait for the warrant.

32:47.433 --> 32:48.699
[ sighs ]

32:50.402 --> 32:52.970
Henry, i thought our appointment
wasn't till friday.

32:52.972 --> 32:56.440
Lewis, i need your help
with a critical matter.

32:56.442 --> 32:58.809
We need to look
at a patient's records.

32:58.811 --> 33:00.610
He's the primary suspect
in a murder investigation.

33:00.612 --> 33:02.646
Now we are waiting
on a warrant, but --

33:02.648 --> 33:07.084
Lives are on the line, so i'm
making a personal request...

33:07.086 --> 33:08.852
As an englishman.

33:08.854 --> 33:10.187
Will you help us?

33:10.189 --> 33:14.391
Since you put it that way,
come in.

33:17.062 --> 33:19.796
Ah, patient's name
is clark walker.

33:19.798 --> 33:21.164
I've heard stories.

33:21.166 --> 33:22.599
He's one of the regulars
here.

33:22.601 --> 33:24.801
What can you tell us?
Raised in the foster system.

33:24.803 --> 33:26.269
No family to speak of.

33:26.271 --> 33:27.704
The original birth records
were destroyed in a fire.

33:27.706 --> 33:29.773
Oh, that's convenient
for an immortal.

33:29.775 --> 33:31.775
Oh, yes,
he thinks he's immortal.

33:31.777 --> 33:32.976
You'll like this one, henry.

33:32.978 --> 33:34.144
He was caught skinny dipping
in the river

33:34.146 --> 33:35.679
On four different occasions.

33:35.681 --> 33:39.616
Ah. [ clears throat ]
the two employees who left --

33:39.618 --> 33:41.752
Was it because
they assaulted clark?

33:41.754 --> 33:43.687
Oh, no, no,
he assaulted them.

33:43.689 --> 33:46.323
Uh, the therapist
has left a note here.

33:46.325 --> 33:49.626
"clark has no fear
of personal harm or death.

33:49.628 --> 33:51.328
He has violent tendencies."

33:51.330 --> 33:52.763
To avoid extended jail time,

33:52.765 --> 33:55.432
He had to agree
to mandatory daily counseling.

33:55.434 --> 33:58.668
Daily?
When's his next session?

34:00.105 --> 34:03.507
[ keys clacking ]

34:03.509 --> 34:05.509
Right now.

34:05.511 --> 34:07.778
N.Y.P.D.

34:07.780 --> 34:09.813
Is there a clark walker here?

34:09.815 --> 34:12.315
[ typing ]

34:12.317 --> 34:14.785
He just signed out.

34:14.787 --> 34:16.486
Lock it down.

34:16.488 --> 34:20.357
Lock it down.
[ buzzes, alarm wailing ]

34:20.359 --> 34:21.691
<i>Man over p.A.: Attention.</i>

34:21.693 --> 34:23.393
<i>Please do not leave</i>
<i>the building</i>

34:23.395 --> 34:24.728
<i>Until further notice.</i>

34:24.730 --> 34:26.530
There, jo.

34:26.532 --> 34:28.065
<i>Please do not leave</i>
<i>the building...</i>

34:28.067 --> 34:29.099
N.Y.P.D.

34:29.101 --> 34:32.102
Excuse me. Stop him!

34:32.104 --> 34:33.637
Stop him!

34:33.639 --> 34:35.605
Excuse me. Watch out.
[ alarm continues wailing ]

34:35.607 --> 34:37.874
<i>Please do not leave</i>
<i>the building</i>

34:37.876 --> 34:39.376
<i>Until further notice.</i>

34:39.378 --> 34:42.079
<i>Attention. Please do not</i>
<i>leave the building...</i>

34:42.081 --> 34:43.613
No!

34:47.286 --> 34:48.785
This is our suspect --
clark walker.

34:48.787 --> 34:51.555
Last seen --
bellevue psychiatric hospital

34:51.557 --> 34:52.689
40 minutes ago.

34:52.691 --> 34:55.692
B.O.L.O. Is out.
Feds and state are looking, too.

34:55.694 --> 35:00.630
But i want him.
This is our suspect. Go get him.

35:02.868 --> 35:06.870
Hey. Don't worry.
We're gonna find him.

35:06.872 --> 35:08.171
Jo...

35:08.173 --> 35:10.507
Yeah?

35:10.509 --> 35:12.576
He worked very hard
to incriminate me.

35:12.578 --> 35:14.311
Did you ever think
it<i> was</i> me?

35:14.313 --> 35:16.680
Henry, you are a lot
of things,

35:16.682 --> 35:19.316
But a killer is not
one of them.

35:19.318 --> 35:22.319
Don't worry.
We've got this covered.

35:22.321 --> 35:25.522
People don't just disappear
in new york these days.

35:25.524 --> 35:27.691
You're safe.

35:29.862 --> 35:31.895
[ door bells jingle ]

35:34.066 --> 35:35.565
Abe?

35:38.170 --> 35:41.171
<i>[ "dies irae" playing ]</i>

35:41.173 --> 35:43.273
Abe?

35:43.275 --> 35:46.409
<i>¶</i> solvet saeclum en favilla<i> ¶</i>

35:46.411 --> 35:49.846
<i>¶</i> teste david cum sybilla<i> ¶</i>

35:51.750 --> 35:56.520
<i>¶</i> quantus tremor est futurus<i> ¶</i>

35:56.522 --> 35:57.621
Abe?

35:57.623 --> 36:00.524
<i>¶</i> quando judex est venturus<i> ¶</i>

36:00.526 --> 36:05.762
<i>¶</i> cuncta stricte discus surus<i> ¶</i>

36:05.764 --> 36:08.832
<i>¶</i> tuba mirum spargens sonum<i> ¶</i>

36:08.834 --> 36:12.602
<i>¶</i> per sepulchra regionum<i> ¶</i>

36:12.604 --> 36:15.639
<i>¶</i> coget omnes ante thronum<i> ¶</i>

36:15.641 --> 36:19.576
<i>¶</i> mors stupebit et natura<i> ¶</i>

36:19.578 --> 36:21.878
<i>¶</i> cum resur--<i> ¶</i>

36:21.880 --> 36:23.413
[ music stops ]

36:28.854 --> 36:32.856
[ floorboard creaks ]

36:32.858 --> 36:37.127
[ breathing heavily ]
where's abraham?

36:37.129 --> 36:41.865
What did you do to him?

36:45.737 --> 36:47.204
What do you want?!

36:47.206 --> 36:49.873
[ blade zings ]
kill me, henry.

36:58.750 --> 37:00.617
With this.

37:05.157 --> 37:06.957
You're insane.

37:12.598 --> 37:14.097
I won't do it.

37:14.099 --> 37:16.366
Abe: [ in distance ] henry!

37:16.368 --> 37:18.368
Henry, you home?

37:18.370 --> 37:20.837
I went to the polish market.

37:20.839 --> 37:25.609
Hey, what do you think
about homemade pierogies?

37:25.611 --> 37:27.711
Henry?

37:27.713 --> 37:30.380
Hey, you there?

37:30.382 --> 37:33.450
[ sword clatters ]
[ grunting ]

37:33.452 --> 37:34.985
[ loud bang ]

37:34.987 --> 37:36.853
What was that?

37:36.855 --> 37:38.121
Aah!
[ bang ]

37:38.123 --> 37:41.658
[ both grunting ]

37:41.660 --> 37:43.426
[ groaning ]

37:43.428 --> 37:45.028
[ thud ]
[ grunting ]

37:45.030 --> 37:46.196
Abe: Henry?

37:46.198 --> 37:49.032
[ both grunting ]

37:49.034 --> 37:50.133
[ whack ]
uhh!

37:50.135 --> 37:51.534
Abe: Henry!

37:51.536 --> 37:53.203
No, abraham, get away!

37:53.205 --> 37:55.472
[ objects clatter ]

37:55.474 --> 37:57.240
Uhh! Ohh!
[ slash ]

37:57.242 --> 37:58.775
[ gasps ]

38:00.812 --> 38:04.881
Uhh. [ gasps ]

38:06.285 --> 38:09.052
[ exhales deeply ]

38:14.059 --> 38:15.825
[ exhaling deeply ]

38:15.827 --> 38:17.394
What the hell?

38:19.364 --> 38:21.631
Is -- is that him?

38:21.633 --> 38:23.767
It doesn't make any sense.

38:23.769 --> 38:27.537
The caller said he was
immortal, but this man is --

38:27.539 --> 38:29.372
Dead.

38:29.374 --> 38:31.508
Very dead.

38:32.644 --> 38:35.312
He wasn't
the anonymous caller.

38:38.750 --> 38:40.850
[ siren wailing in distance ]

38:40.852 --> 38:44.487
[ coldplay's "have yourself a
merry little christmas" plays ]

38:50.529 --> 38:52.562
Is there anything else
you noticed?

38:52.564 --> 38:54.831
The smallest details
can really help.

38:54.833 --> 38:57.434
Hey, give him a break.
He's one of us.
[ pats arm ]

38:57.436 --> 39:02.372
He'll, uh, he'll talk
when he's ready. Thanks.

39:02.374 --> 39:04.708
You did good, doc --

39:04.710 --> 39:06.776
Taking out a serial killer.

39:06.778 --> 39:11.548
Listen...
It was a righteous kill.

39:11.550 --> 39:15.051
¶ ...Will be out of sight ¶

39:20.158 --> 39:22.659
¶ have yourself ¶

39:22.661 --> 39:26.296
¶ a merry little christmas ¶

39:26.298 --> 39:31.835
¶ make the yuletide gay ¶

39:31.837 --> 39:36.172
¶ from now on our troubles ¶

39:36.174 --> 39:41.611
¶ will be far away ¶

39:42.547 --> 39:45.048
[ siren wailing in distance ]

39:45.050 --> 39:48.118
¶ here we are ¶

39:48.120 --> 39:50.253
¶ as in olden days ¶

39:50.255 --> 39:52.322
¶ happy golden days ¶

39:52.324 --> 39:54.758
You know, a wise man
once told me

39:54.760 --> 39:58.428
The day when killing someone
doesn't affect you --

39:58.430 --> 40:02.165
That's the day
you got real problems.

40:02.167 --> 40:03.733
I wouldn't listen to him.

40:03.735 --> 40:05.301
He doesn't know
what he's talking about.

40:05.303 --> 40:07.604
I disagree.

40:09.141 --> 40:12.776
When you're ready to talk,
i'm here. We all are.

40:12.778 --> 40:15.145
¶ we all will be together ¶

40:15.147 --> 40:18.081
[ siren wailing ]

40:18.083 --> 40:21.217
¶ if the fates allow ¶

40:21.219 --> 40:22.886
<i>Henry: We all have secrets.</i>

40:22.888 --> 40:25.355
<i>There's nothing wrong</i>
<i>with that.</i>

40:25.357 --> 40:27.056
<i>But we all need a confidante,</i>

40:27.058 --> 40:30.193
<i>A friend to share</i>
<i>our secrets with.</i>

40:30.195 --> 40:32.629
<i>In a way, the shared secret</i>
<i>tells us</i>

40:32.631 --> 40:34.898
<i>Who our real friends are.</i>

40:34.900 --> 40:37.167
<i>They're the people</i>
<i>we entrust the most.</i>

40:37.169 --> 40:40.403
[ telephone rings ]

40:40.405 --> 40:43.540
¶ a merry little christmas ¶

40:43.542 --> 40:48.745
¶ now ¶
[ ring ]

40:50.615 --> 40:54.184
Man: So you're wondering
what happened.

40:54.186 --> 40:56.453
He wasn't you.

40:56.455 --> 41:00.023
Mm. Perhaps i gave poor clark
the impression

41:00.025 --> 41:03.026
We could pass on
our affliction.

41:03.028 --> 41:04.527
Thankfully, we can't.

41:04.529 --> 41:06.329
Clark was
a full-blown psychopath,

41:06.331 --> 41:08.932
And if allowed more time,
he would have killed again.

41:08.934 --> 41:13.269
You did a good deed,
if you don't mind me saying.

41:13.271 --> 41:16.339
Why? Why do this?

41:16.341 --> 41:19.676
After 200 years, you just did
something for the first time.

41:19.678 --> 41:22.111
You killed a man.

41:22.113 --> 41:25.715
There's no other rush like it,
taking a life.

41:25.717 --> 41:29.018
It's thrilling.
Tell me i'm wrong.

41:29.020 --> 41:30.854
I'm done with this.

41:30.856 --> 41:36.493
You're just as sick as the man
you sent here to kill me.

41:36.495 --> 41:40.363
That's why you hide.

41:40.365 --> 41:42.599
You're insane.

41:42.601 --> 41:46.035
Look outside.

41:48.974 --> 41:52.041
[ window whirs ]

41:53.245 --> 41:56.212
[ american accent ]
in my professional opinion,

41:56.214 --> 41:57.580
I disagree.

41:57.582 --> 42:00.350
I'm leaving town for a while,

42:00.352 --> 42:06.189
But i do look forward to
continuing our conversation.

42:10.829 --> 42:12.862
Merry christmas, henry.

42:17.335 --> 42:18.835
[ whirs ]
